SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The Association follows accounting principles generally accepted in the United States of America related to the accounting for uncertainty in income taxes. This guidance sets a minimum threshold for financial statement recognition of the benefit of a tax position taken or expected to be taken in a tax return. Tax positions for the open tax years as of December 31, 2022 were reviewed, and it was determined that no provision for uncertain tax positions is required.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section A, line 7a
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The AISWCD is made up of 16 councils as its organizational structure. Each council is comprised of four to eight SWCD's who have joined together based on similar interest and geographic conditions. Members of the AISWCD Board of Directors are elected by the districts that comprise each council. Each council elects one delgate as a board member and one alternate board member. The alternate does not have voting authority unless the delegate cannot participate. Each year at the annual meeting of the members, the voting body elects three to four officers. It is the right and the responsibility of the board to govern the activities of the association, to approve the AISWCD's annual budget as acceptable to be subject to approval by the voting body of members SWCD's and to approve expenses of the AISWCD.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section A, line 7b
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: SWCD's have the right to bring forth resolutions that are subject to approval, first at the council level, second at the Board of Directors level and finally by the voting body at the Annual Meeting. Regardless of the decisions of the council and the Board of Directors, the voting body at the annual meeting has the final decision as to whether a resolution passes or fails. Resolutions that have been approved by a majority of the voting body at the annual meeting become part of the annual plan of work of the AISWCD. The voting body of the annual meeting also has the responsibility of approving the AISWCD's annual operating budget.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 11b
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The 990 is prepared by a CPA, reviewed by management, and made available to the board for review.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 12c
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: On an annual basis directors, officers, and staff members are required to submit a disclosure statment to the Board of Directors. If a conflict exists the individual is not allowed to vote on the matter.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section C, line 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The governing documents are made available to the public upon request.
